<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="arm-vt">arm <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɑːm/    美 /ɑːrm/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>用武器装备：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>These security guards <strong>armed</strong> themselves <strong>with</strong> guns.
这些保安配有枪支。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-equip">2.★ <strong>提供；配备 (equip)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The book <strong>arms</strong> the reader <strong>with</strong> a mass of useful information. 
这本书为读者提供大量有用的信息。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>armed /ɑːrmd/ adj <br />
1. ★ <strong>武装的；持枪的：</strong><br />
反 unarmed </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>armed police</strong>
武装警察</p></div>

<ol>
<li><strong>具备 (足够的知识、技能或装备) 的：</strong>  </li>
</ol>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A birdwatcher, <strong>armed with</strong> a telescope, found a bird sitting on a rock.
观鸟者带着望远镜，看到岩石上落着一只鸟。</p><footer>2015 陕西改</footer></div></div>